overview: The user wanted to significantly improve the aesthetics of their sleep
  questionnaire app, moving it from a generic look to a more calming and
  professional sleep-themed design. I started by conducting a thorough code
  review of existing styling and identified several areas for improvement,
  including the color palette, layout, and component styling. The approach
  involved implementing a new sleep-themed color palette using OKLCH for
  perceptual uniformity, redesigning the main form layout with subtle background
  elements and an enhanced progress indicator, and updating all UI components
  and questionnaire sections for visual consistency. Key decisions included
  using custom CSS utility classes for gradients and shadows, and applying
  consistent card-style groupings across all form sections. During the process,
  a console error related to  values in input fields was identified and
  fixed by modifying the  component to safely handle such values. The
  outcome is a visually cohesive and aesthetically pleasing application that
  aligns with the user's request for a "beautiful" design.
